    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Vibration Damper, Crankshaft,
        Main Bearings, Flywheel, and Crankcase - Remove - Remove Crankshaft and Main Bearings
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210010702.11" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>Remove Crankshaft and Main Bearings</title>
        <step1>
            <para id="s210010702.11.1" count="1">Rotate engine stand so crankshaft is on top and horizontal.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Verify bearing caps and crankcase are stamped to identify location. Stamp crankcase oil pan
                rail and main bearing caps on camshaft side. Stamp in numerical order; number caps from 1 through 7,
                starting with 1 at front of engine.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010732" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8546.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Main bearing cap numbers</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Number stamp location</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bearing cap</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove main bearing cap bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010733" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8537.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Remove main bearing cap bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Grasp main bearing cap and rock back and forth to loosen, remove cap. Bearing cap bolts may
                be used to rock cap as necessary.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Use only hand pressure when rocking caps during removal.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove lower bearing shell from main bearing cap and keep in order with bearing cap for
                inspection.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the two rear thrust bearing, bearing 7, mounting bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Grasp bearing cap 7 and rock back and forth to loosen, remove cap. Bearing cap bolts may be
                used to rock cap as necessary.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Use only hand pressure when rocking caps during removal.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010734" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8541.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Remove rear thrust bearing (bearing 7)</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To avoid possible engine or vehicle damage, do not bind, bend, drop, or gouge crankshaft.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove crankshaft from crankcase using an appropriate lifting sling. Keep crankshaft level
                to prevent binding. Do not drop or gouge crankshaft during removal. Set crankshaft on a protected
                surface and prevent it from falling or rolling.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010735" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5359.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Lift crankshaft</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove upper main bearing shells. Push bearing shells out of main bearing saddle. Mark upper
                shells and put with lower shells.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010736" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5362.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Remove upper main bearing shells</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
